Reference-contexts: Profit represents an attempt to overcome these difficulties, by providing programming language support for developing applications with such soft real time requirements. Profit is a coordination language <ref> [1] </ref> built on top of the C computation language. The low-level analytic algorithms are implemented using conventional C statements and data structures, and Profit adds the communication, synchronization, multi-threading and timing facilities. Profit is intended for use by sophisticated programmers to construct distributed financial services applications.
