Reference-contexts: Agents can contain arbitrary knowledge and they may carry out arbitrary computations. In fact, the knowledge in the agents could be updated dynamically. For example, the thresholds used by certain rules in agents could be updated as the market fluctuates to capture changes in trends <ref> [5] </ref>. Agents are implemented in SPLENDORS using Profit facets. Agents are conceptually associated with securities in portfolios making it possible for different portfolios containing the same security to have 6 different agents.
